headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo scored 30 points and had 11 rebounds and the Miami Heat beat the Indiana Pacers 124-111 on Friday night in NBA Cup play.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo scores 30 to propel Heat past Pacers 124-111

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner had 31 points and 11 rebounds, Jalen Suggs added 19 points and seven rebounds, and the Orlando Magic pulled away in the fourth quarter to a 98-86 win over the Philadelphia 76ers in an NBA Cup game Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic win 98-86 in NBA Cup game, dropping 76ers to 2-10 overall

headlines.description: — Malik Beasley scored seven of his 20 points in the fourth quarter, Cade Cunningham had 15 points and 10 assists and the Detroit Pistons beat the struggling Toronto Raptors 99-95 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons beat Raptors 99-95 to remain undefeated in NBA Cup play

headlines.description: — Dyson Daniels continued his scoring surge with 25 points and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Washington Wizards 129-117 on Friday night to improve to 2-0 in the NBA Cup.
headlines.shortLinkText: Daniels continues scoring surge with 25 points as Hawks beat Wizards and move to 2-0 in NBA Cup

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored a season-high 37 points, Darius Garland had 29 and the Cleveland Cavaliers continued one of the best starts in league history, improving to 14-0 with a 144-126 win over the Chicago Bulls on Friday night in an NBA Cup game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 37, Cavaliers stay perfect and improve to 14-0 with 144-126 win over Bulls

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at New York Knicks
Los Angeles Lakers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 40 points and 12 rebounds, LeBron James had 15 points, 16 rebounds and 12 assists and the Los Angeles Lakers opened defense of their Emirates NBA Cup title with a 120-115 victory over the San Antonio Spurs on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis, LeBron James lead Lakers past Spurs 120-115 to open NBA Cup title defense

headlines.description: — Jabari Smith Jr. had a season-high 28 points with five 3-pointers and the Houston Rockets never trailed in a 125-104 rout of the Los Angeles Clippers on Friday night in their NBA Cup opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jabari Smith Jr. has season-high 28 points as Rockets rout Clippers 125-104 in NBA Cup play

events.name: Denver Nuggets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored 29 points to lift the New Orleans Pelicans to a 101-94 victory Friday night over the Denver Nuggets, who played without three-time MVP...
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram leads Pelicans past Jokic-less Nuggets, 101-94

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 28 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the short-handed Phoenix Suns 99-83 on Friday night in an NBA Cup game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores 28 points, Thunder beat Suns 99-83 in NBA Cup

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Draymond Green had 13 points, eight rebounds and seven assists before a late ejection after two technical fouls in a 33-second span, and the Golden State Warriors beat the Memphis Grizzlies 123-118 on Friday night in a physical NBA Cup game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Draymond Green and Stephen Curry lead balanced Warriors past Grizzlies 123-118

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards had 36 points, and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the short-handed Sacramento Kings 130-126 in overtime on Friday night despite a franchise-record 60 points from De’Aaron Fox.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards, Timberwolves beat Kings 130-126 in OT despite franchise-record 60 points from De'Aaron Fox
